    "narrative": "The Austin Waves enter today\u2019s slate with **Kyle Tucker** (83.19) leading the charge as the premier option. Facing Lorenzen, **Kyle Tucker** benefits from a massive 14% park factor boost and a favorable platoon matchup, solidifying his role as the cornerstone of our lineup. **Jacob Wilson** (74.08) follows closely behind, with his elite 10% park factor and the 19% boost from facing a struggling Schultz (5.06 xERA) making him a high-efficiency start. Similarly, **Andy Pages** (68.47) and **Miguel Vargas** (66.33) are locked in as strong plays, with the latter gaining an edge due to a slow opposing delivery that increases his stolen base potential\u2014a critical consideration for our strategy given our emphasis on scarcity.\n\nThe most difficult roster decision today was excluding **Nolan Schanuel** (55.84) from the starting nine. While **Nolan Schanuel** provides a solid floor, his projected efficiency fell just short of **Josh Lowe** (60.13), whose dynamic platoon edge against King provided the necessary margin to claim the final outfield spot. We are also closely monitoring the high-ceiling potential of **Marcell Ozuna** (65.09); despite the tough matchup against McClanahan, the wind blowing out adds a volatility factor that favors his power profile, pushing him into the utility slot over other bench options like **Heliot Ramos** (53.59) or **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** (49.38).\n\nRisk management remains a priority given the volatility of our lower-tier starters. **Drake Baldwin** (56.63) and **Gunnar Henderson** (54.20) are currently hovering in the marginal category. Specifically, **Gunnar Henderson** faces a significant 15% penalty due to the platoon disadvantage against Cantillo, and we are tracking his performance closely to ensure he does not become a drain on our efficiency caps. While **Jackson Merrill** (53.94) projects a total score of zero against his opposing pitcher, the raw batting potential still keeps him active for now, though his usage is under constant review should his plate discipline metrics flag further.",
